<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000013#     1#        908.2#">Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-908.2</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_13.1-908.2"/><heading><desig>§ 13.1-908.2.</desig><title>Court proceedings</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A dissolved corporation that has published a notice under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 13.1-908.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-908.1">§ 13.1-908.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000013#     1#        908.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> may file an application with the circuit court of the city or county where the dissolved corporation's principal office, or, if none in the Commonwealth, its registered office, is or was last located for a determination of the amount and form of security to be provided for payment of claims that are contingent or have not been made known to the dissolved corporation or that are based on an event occurring after the effective date of dissolution but that, based on the facts known to the dissolved corporation, are reasonably estimated to arise after the effective date of dissolution. Provision need not be made for any claim that is or is reasonably anticipated to be barred under subsection C of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 13.1-908.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-908.1">§ 13.1-908.1.<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000013#     1#        908.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation></p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Within 10 days after the filing of the application, notice of the proceeding shall be given by the dissolved corporation to each claimant holding a contingent claim whose contingent claim is shown on the records of the dissolved corporation.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The court may appoint a guardian ad litem to represent all claimants whose identities are unknown in any proceeding brought under this section. The reasonable fees and expenses of such guardian, including all reasonable expert witness fees, shall be paid by the dissolved corporation.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_d"/><heading><desig>D.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Provision by the dissolved corporation for security in the amount and the form ordered by the court under subsection A shall satisfy the dissolved corporation's obligations with respect to claims that do not meet the definition of a claim in subsection D of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 13.1-908"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-908">§ 13.1-908<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000013#     1#          908#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and such claims may not be enforced against a member who received assets in liquidation.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2007 VA CH 925"><content><span normalizedCite="2007 Va. Ch. 925">2007, c. 925<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2007#000925#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PVJ0-004G-K0NK-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 13.1.</desig><title>CORPORATIONS</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 10.</desig><title>VIRGINIA NONSTOCK CORPORATION ACT</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 13.</desig><title>DISSOLUTION</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Business &amp; Corporate Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QjA4OEVGODBENzY4NDcxM0IyQzA1OTEwQzVDODRBOUE7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Creditor Rights</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6M0E3NTk4NDNCNTI0NDg0RTkzRjk3RDAyMzAwNTRDRjE7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MzIwNDg1OThGRUI4NDc4RkFDRTZENTc0RkU4QzlENkU</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NjI3NzU1NjMwN0RBNEE5QTk4MUZCNkVCMDNFMzUzMkE7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OTZDNjlCQzhGMzk2NEM5NkFFQUQ2OUEzMERFMEJGRTc</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Involuntary Dissolution</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MkRDRkNERjFFQTE2NDlFNjk3M0REMjlFRjM3Nzg0QTc7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OTZDNjlCQzhGMzk2NEM5NkFFQUQ2OUEzMERFMEJGRTc